
[1]digestive

   DIGESTIVE, a.

   1. Having the power to cause digestion in the stomach; as a digestive
   preparation or medicine.

   2. Capable of softening and preparing by heat.

   3. Methodizing; reducing to order; as digestive thought.

   4. Causing maturation in wounds or ulcers.

   5. Dissolving.

                                DIGESTIVE, n.

   1. In medicine, any preparation or medicine which increases the tone of
   the stomach, and aids digestion; a stomachic; a corroborant.

   2. In surgery, an application which ripens an ulcer or wound, or
   disposes it to suppurate.

   Digestive salt, the muriate of potash.
